1
00:00:02.002 --> 00:00:02.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ROM: What do you think?

2
00:00:03.002 --> 00:00:04.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LEETA: I don't know.

3
00:00:04.754 --> 00:00:05.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

4
00:00:06.881 --> 00:00:08.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I like it.

5
00:00:10.051 --> 00:00:11.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you?

6
00:00:11.469 --> 00:00:14.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Rom, it's two handkerchiefs
and a loincloth.

7
00:00:14.764 --> 00:00:17.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose we could lose the handkerchiefs.

8
00:00:17.767 --> 00:00:22.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ferengi tradition or no Ferengi tradition,
I am not going to be naked at my wedding.

9
00:00:22.439 --> 00:00:24.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who said anything about naked?

10
00:00:24.357 --> 00:00:26.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll still have the loincloth.

11
00:00:28.611 --> 00:00:30.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please show us something else.

12
00:00:30.155 --> 00:00:31.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is nothing else.

13
00:00:31.990 --> 00:00:34.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've shown you 153
different wedding dresses,

14
00:00:35.035 --> 00:00:38.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
from Tellarite modern
to Risian traditional,

15
00:00:38.413 --> 00:00:39.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and you've hated them all.

16
00:00:39.914 --> 00:00:42.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I like number 38.

17
00:00:43.001 --> 00:00:44.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Number 38?

18
00:00:44.335 --> 00:00:47.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It had more layers
than a Baduviam tapestry.

19
00:00:47.338 --> 00:00:49.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It was elegant.
-It was bulky.

20
00:00:50.008 --> 00:00:51.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I liked 64.

21
00:00:51.926 --> 00:00:53.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sixty-four?
-( exclaims in disgust )

22
00:00:53.970 --> 00:00:56.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, at least they agree on something.

23
00:00:57.307 --> 00:01:00.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you just let Garak
design a dress on his own?

24
00:01:01.269 --> 00:01:03.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know whatever he comes up with
will be beautiful.

25
00:01:03.688 --> 00:01:07.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My dear, I find your blind adoration
both flattering and disturbing.

26
00:01:08.026 --> 00:01:09.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But she does have a point.

27
00:01:09.652 --> 00:01:10.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: Leeta!

28
00:01:10.695 --> 00:01:13.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That 15-minute break you asked for
was up an hour ago.

29
00:01:13.615 --> 00:01:15.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Brother, what do you think of this dress?

30
00:01:17.285 --> 00:01:19.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't want to think about it.

31
00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:22.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All I know is that any marriage

32
00:01:22.207 --> 00:01:27.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where the female is allowed to speak
and wear clothing is doomed to failure.

33
00:01:29.422 --> 00:01:31.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your dabo table awaits.

34
00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:33.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exclaims angrily )

35
00:01:34.636 --> 00:01:35.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There he is.

36
00:01:37.263 --> 00:01:38.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's talk to him.

37
00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:40.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now?

38
00:01:40.683 --> 00:01:42.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Rom.

39
00:01:42.560 --> 00:01:44.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Keiko and the kids
will be a lot safer on Earth

40
00:01:44.813 --> 00:01:46.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
than they are here.

41
00:01:46.606 --> 00:01:49.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've only been gone two days,
and I miss them already.

42
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:52.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Still, don't you feel better
knowing they're out of harm's way?

43
00:01:52.654 --> 00:01:55.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish I could convince Jake
to visit Earth for a while.

44
00:01:55.698 --> 00:01:58.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain. Can we speak to you for a moment?

45
00:01:58.451 --> 00:01:59.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you're not too busy.

46
00:01:59.744 --> 00:02:01.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. Go ahead.

47
00:02:03.289 --> 00:02:04.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Would you marry me?

48
00:02:05.542 --> 00:02:06.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean us.

49
00:02:07.043 --> 00:02:11.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, would you perform
our wedding ceremony?

50
00:02:12.507 --> 00:02:15.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would be a great honor
to be married by the Emissary.

51
00:02:15.135 --> 00:02:19.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not for another two weeks,
so you have plenty of time to get ready.

52
00:02:19.639 --> 00:02:22.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess I'll have to start
brushing up on my Bajoran.

53
00:02:23.434 --> 00:02:24.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

54
00:02:25.103 --> 00:02:27.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Captain?
-If you'll excuse me?

55
00:02:35.864 --> 00:02:37.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe they're not coming.

56
00:02:37.532 --> 00:02:39.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That would be a nice surprise.

57
00:02:45.874 --> 00:02:49.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One thing I'll say for the Dominion...
they're punctual.

58
00:02:49.919 --> 00:02:52.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's the fifth convoy
headed for Cardassia

59
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:54.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in the last five weeks.

60
00:02:54.173 --> 00:02:57.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can only imagine how many Jem'Hadar
soldiers are stationed there now.

61
00:02:57.343 --> 00:02:58.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Too many.

62
00:03:00.305 --> 00:03:03.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish they'd just attack
and get it over with.

63
00:03:03.099 --> 00:03:05.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have the feeling you're
going to get your wish.

64
00:05:07.181 --> 00:05:09.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks for the invite, Dad.

65
00:05:09.809 --> 00:05:13.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I haven't had a home-cooked meal since--
-Since the last time you were here.

66
00:05:14.564 --> 00:05:16.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Sounds about right.

67
00:05:16.316 --> 00:05:18.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
So, uh, what's for dinner?

68
00:05:19.235 --> 00:05:22.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Ah. Can I get some salsa with that?

69
00:05:22.739 --> 00:05:23.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Read the headline.

70
00:05:25.116 --> 00:05:28.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
"Bajorans Continue Negotiations
with Dominion."

71
00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:29.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Go on.

72
00:05:30.663 --> 00:05:33.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
"Station Commander
Opposes Nonaggression Pact."

73
00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:34.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And the byline.

74
00:05:37.003 --> 00:05:38.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
"By Jake Sisko."

75
00:05:41.841 --> 00:05:43.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You should have warned me.

76
00:05:44.093 --> 00:05:45.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I was waiting for the right moment.

77
00:05:45.678 --> 00:05:48.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The right moment was before
you published the article.

78
00:05:48.598 --> 00:05:51.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I know. I'm sorry.

79
00:05:51.517 --> 00:05:53.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
But aren't you glad I got a job?

80
00:05:53.644 --> 00:05:55.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You mean, this isn't a one-time thing?

81
00:05:55.813 --> 00:05:59.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Nope. I'm now an official correspondent
for the Starfleet News Service.

82
00:06:00.943 --> 00:06:02.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, what about your novel?

83
00:06:02.320 --> 00:06:03.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm not giving up on it,

84
00:06:03.863 --> 00:06:06.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
but, this way,
I get to see my work in print.

85
00:06:06.240 --> 00:06:09.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And, apparently, I get to see
everything I say in print, too.

86
00:06:09.368 --> 00:06:12.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
( scoffs ) You're a public figure, Dad.

87
00:06:12.205 --> 00:06:14.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're the Captain
of the most important space station

88
00:06:14.749 --> 00:06:16.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
in the entire Federation.

89
00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:17.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're news.

90
00:06:17.335 --> 00:06:18.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Don't remind me.

91
00:06:24.759 --> 00:06:27.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess I can't stop you
from doing your job.

92
00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:29.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I quote you on that?

93
00:06:30.848 --> 00:06:33.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
( clears throat softly ) I guess not.

94
00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:38.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Yamok sauce.

95
00:06:38.272 --> 00:06:40.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Who would bother to smuggle in

96
00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:43.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
10,000 wrappages
of Cardassian yamok sauce?

97
00:06:44.612 --> 00:06:46.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Oh. Quark.

98
00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:47.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
That little worm.

99
00:06:48.074 --> 00:06:50.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
He thinks the Cardassians
are going to retake the station.

100
00:06:50.118 --> 00:06:53.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
He's a Ferengi.
You can't blame him for hedging his bets.

101
00:06:53.287 --> 00:06:55.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
But it is a lot of yamok sauce.

102
00:06:56.165 --> 00:06:58.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
What is a yamok, anyway?

103
00:06:59.585 --> 00:07:01.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
What would you like me to do with it?

104
00:07:03.548 --> 00:07:04.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Major?

105
00:07:05.341 --> 00:07:06.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't care. You decide.

106
00:07:08.302 --> 00:07:09.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dump it.

107
00:07:10.054 --> 00:07:11.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very good.

108
00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:16.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Would you mind telling me what's going on?

109
00:07:16.227 --> 00:07:18.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-What do you mean?
-You and Odo.

110
00:07:18.646 --> 00:07:20.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You've been avoiding each other for weeks.

111
00:07:20.189 --> 00:07:22.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Oh, it's a long story.
-Those are the best kind.

112
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:28.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighing ) Odo has... feelings for me.

113
00:07:29.031 --> 00:07:32.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What kind of feelings?
-The kind that aren't easy to talk about.

114
00:07:32.827 --> 00:07:33.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since when?

115
00:07:33.870 --> 00:07:35.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since, I don't know-- years.

116
00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:37.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just found out about it last month.

117
00:07:37.957 --> 00:07:39.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That explains a lot.

118
00:07:39.208 --> 00:07:41.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It does?
-Not really.

119
00:07:41.878 --> 00:07:45.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It just seemed
like the right thing to say.

120
00:07:46.507 --> 00:07:49.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I had no idea.
-Neither did I.

121
00:07:52.847 --> 00:07:55.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
60 degrees Celsius--
just the way you like it.

122
00:08:00.354 --> 00:08:02.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, sir...

123
00:08:02.190 --> 00:08:04.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is it true what they're saying
about the Romulans?

124
00:08:05.651 --> 00:08:06.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do they say?

125
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:10.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, there were some Orion Free Traders
in Quark's last night,

126
00:08:10.531 --> 00:08:11.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they heard from a Vulcan diplomat

127
00:08:12.074 --> 00:08:13.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that the Romulans

128
00:08:13.784 --> 00:08:16.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
signed a nonaggression pact
with the Dominion.

129
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A lot of rumors float around
at a time like this, Cadet.

130
00:08:19.665 --> 00:08:22.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just don't forget
the 190th Rule of Acquisition.

131
00:08:23.878 --> 00:08:25.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"Hear all, trust nothing."

132
00:08:26.714 --> 00:08:28.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good advice, sir.

133
00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:38.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Romulans.

134
00:08:40.937 --> 00:08:42.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko to Dax.

135
00:08:42.396 --> 00:08:43.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Dax here.</i>

136
00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:46.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Put me through to Starfleet Intelligence.

137
00:08:47.401 --> 00:08:48.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Romulans!

138
00:08:48.736 --> 00:08:50.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I always knew they were without honor!

139
00:08:50.696 --> 00:08:51.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now they have proven it.

140
00:08:51.739 --> 00:08:53.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When did they sign the treaty?

141
00:08:53.324 --> 00:08:56.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yesterday. They must
be desperate to side with the Dominion.

142
00:08:56.410 --> 00:08:57.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Technically,
they're not siding with anyone.

143
00:08:58.079 --> 00:08:59.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a nonaggression pact.

144
00:08:59.789 --> 00:09:02.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which means if the Dominion attacks,
they just sit by and do nothing.

145
00:09:02.750 --> 00:09:05.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Romulans,
the Miradorn, the Tholians...

146
00:09:06.879 --> 00:09:10.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Dominion is making impressive inroads
in the Alpha Quadrant.

147
00:09:10.716 --> 00:09:12.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the Bajorans are
still talking to them?

148
00:09:12.468 --> 00:09:16.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My people will never sign that treaty
or any other agreement with the Dominion.

149
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:19.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Meanwhile, more Jem'Hadar ships
come through the wormhole every week.

150
00:09:19.600 --> 00:09:21.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It must stop.

151
00:09:21.143 --> 00:09:22.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's going to stop.

152
00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:25.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've talked to Starfleet Command.

153
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:29.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've agreed that no more Dominion ships
can be allowed into the Alpha Quadrant.

154
00:09:29.235 --> 00:09:30.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How do we keep them out?

155
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:32.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're going to mine
the entrance to the wormhole.

156
00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:36.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prevent the Dominion from bringing
any more reinforcements to Cardassia.

157
00:09:36.951 --> 00:09:40.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we try to stop those convoys,
it may very well start a war.

158
00:09:40.913 --> 00:09:42.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe so...

159
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:44.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but one thing is certain.

160
00:09:44.208 --> 00:09:45.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're losing the peace,

161
00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:50.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
which means a war could be our only hope.

162
00:09:57.888 --> 00:09:59.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about pulse mines?

163
00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:02.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could equip them
with variable geometry detonators.

164
00:10:02.351 --> 00:10:03.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Not good enough.

165
00:10:03.644 --> 00:10:05.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dominion ships can wait
at the mouth of the wormhole

166
00:10:05.688 --> 00:10:06.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and pick them off one by one.

167
00:10:07.064 --> 00:10:08.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if we cloaked them?

168
00:10:08.733 --> 00:10:10.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Cloaking doesn't always work
against the Dominion.

169
00:10:10.943 --> 00:10:14.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe cloaked ships don't,
but I'm thinking much smaller...

170
00:10:14.447 --> 00:10:16.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
each mine no more than a meter across.

171
00:10:18.034 --> 00:10:20.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, mines that small
don't have a lot of power.

172
00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:23.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would take dozens of them
to disable a warship.

173
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:27.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'd run out of mines
before they ran out of ships.

174
00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom! Are you here?

175
00:10:31.797 --> 00:10:35.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Cloak. Small. Dozens."
I heard every word.

176
00:10:35.718 --> 00:10:38.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, something's wrong.
You haven't touched your food.

177
00:10:38.220 --> 00:10:39.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's my stomach.

178
00:10:39.972 --> 00:10:42.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ever since Captain Sisko agreed
to officiate at our wedding,

179
00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:43.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't had much of an appetite.

180
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:46.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you wanted
Captain Sisko to marry you.

181
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:50.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I did, but now that he said yes,
it's become so...

182
00:10:52.276 --> 00:10:53.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
real.

183
00:10:55.863 --> 00:10:57.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to get married!

184
00:10:57.490 --> 00:11:00.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not for another two weeks,
and in the meantime, we have work to do.

185
00:11:00.785 --> 00:11:03.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if Leeta turns out
to be just like Nog's mother?

186
00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:04.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if I can't make her happy?

187
00:11:04.872 --> 00:11:06.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if this is
the biggest mistake of my life?

188
00:11:06.457 --> 00:11:07.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What if--
-Rom!

189
00:11:12.213 --> 00:11:14.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Self-replication.

190
00:11:14.382 --> 00:11:15.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's the only answer.

191
00:11:16.717 --> 00:11:17.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Self-replication?

192
00:11:18.552 --> 00:11:21.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the mines are going to be small,
we'll need a lot of them,

193
00:11:21.430 --> 00:11:23.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we'll need a way
to replace them quickly

194
00:11:23.474 --> 00:11:26.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
if the Jem'Hadar try to blast
their way through, and...

195
00:11:26.852 --> 00:11:29.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh-oh. I forgot to request new quarters.

196
00:11:30.147 --> 00:11:31.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mine are too small.

197
00:11:31.148 --> 00:11:32.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are Leeta and I going to live?

198
00:11:32.858 --> 00:11:34.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom, I think you're on to something.

199
00:11:34.276 --> 00:11:36.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know I am.
I've measured them three times.

200
00:11:36.612 --> 00:11:38.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nowhere to put her prayer mandala.

201
00:11:38.197 --> 00:11:40.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could equip each mine
with a replicator unit.

202
00:11:40.491 --> 00:11:42.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No matter how many
the Jem'Hadar destroyed,

203
00:11:42.243 --> 00:11:43.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
there'd always be more.

204
00:11:43.411 --> 00:11:46.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'd program them to swarm detonate...
20 or 30 mines to each ship.

205
00:11:47.081 --> 00:11:48.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The only problem is you'll have to wait

206
00:11:49.041 --> 00:11:51.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
until the entire mine field
is deployed before you activate it.

207
00:11:51.710 --> 00:11:55.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Otherwise, the proximity sensors
could cause premature detonation.

208
00:11:56.507 --> 00:11:58.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Where's Leeta going to put
all her clothes?

209
00:11:58.676 --> 00:12:01.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't have enough closet space.

210
00:12:01.178 --> 00:12:04.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I better go talk to Sisko.
-I'll go draw up some specs.

211
00:12:04.098 --> 00:12:06.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got to go to waste extraction.

212
00:12:07.435 --> 00:12:09.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What did Starfleet Command say?

213
00:12:09.311 --> 00:12:10.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many reinforcements
will they be sending?

214
00:12:11.063 --> 00:12:12.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
KIRA: And how soon will they get here?

215
00:12:12.523 --> 00:12:14.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not getting any reinforcements.

216
00:12:14.483 --> 00:12:16.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll have to make do with what we've got.

217
00:12:17.778 --> 00:12:19.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What we've got isn't enough.

218
00:12:19.238 --> 00:12:21.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir, as Strategic Operations Officer,

219
00:12:21.115 --> 00:12:22.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I cannot guarantee
the safety of this station

220
00:12:23.075 --> 00:12:24.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if the Dominion fleet attacks.

221
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:26.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your concerns are noted, Commander.

222
00:12:26.370 --> 00:12:27.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's Starfleet thinking?

223
00:12:28.581 --> 00:12:31.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They must have given you a reason
for denying your request.

224
00:12:31.500 --> 00:12:32.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They did.
-And?

225
00:12:33.919 --> 00:12:35.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not at liberty to discuss it.

226
00:12:36.464 --> 00:12:37.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's just say

227
00:12:38.007 --> 00:12:40.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet's resources
will be needed elsewhere.

228
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:43.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What could be more important
than defending this station?

229
00:12:43.512 --> 00:12:45.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is not for us to decide.

230
00:12:45.389 --> 00:12:47.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are our orders, Captain?

231
00:12:47.141 --> 00:12:49.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Deploy the minefield and prepare
for a Dominion attack.

232
00:12:49.810 --> 00:12:51.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And when the attack comes?

233
00:12:51.520 --> 00:12:53.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then we are to defend the station

234
00:12:53.272 --> 00:12:55.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
until the mines are in position
and the field has been activated.

235
00:12:56.025 --> 00:12:58.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The <i>Defiant </i>will be unable
to raise shields or cloak

236
00:12:58.861 --> 00:13:00.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
while deploying the mines.

237
00:13:00.237 --> 00:13:01.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will be an easy target.

238
00:13:01.530 --> 00:13:04.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then it's up to DS9 to defend her.

239
00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:08.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the Dominion wants to stop the <i>Defiant,</i>
they'll have to come through us.

240
00:13:13.292 --> 00:13:14.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me, Constable?

241
00:13:15.503 --> 00:13:17.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major, I'd like your permission

242
00:13:17.421 --> 00:13:20.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to terminate all outgoing
subspace communications.

243
00:13:21.550 --> 00:13:23.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really think that's necessary?

244
00:13:23.886 --> 00:13:25.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no time for security leaks.

245
00:13:25.930 --> 00:13:30.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've prepared a number of false messages
we can transmit at random intervals

246
00:13:31.060 --> 00:13:35.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so there won't be any noticeable drop
in our outgoing subspace traffic.

247
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:36.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll see what I can do.

248
00:13:37.775 --> 00:13:39.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd appreciate that.

249
00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:41.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major...

250
00:13:43.948 --> 00:13:45.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

251
00:13:48.744 --> 00:13:50.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's something you ought to know.

252
00:13:51.789 --> 00:13:52.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

253
00:13:53.874 --> 00:13:57.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been thinking about
asking you out to dinner.

254
00:14:05.803 --> 00:14:07.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been expecting something like this.

255
00:14:07.930 --> 00:14:09.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could tell.

256
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:13.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've looked a little uncomfortable
around me lately.

257
00:14:13.435 --> 00:14:15.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you've looked
a little uncomfortable yourself.

258
00:14:18.440 --> 00:14:21.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which is why I wanted you to know
I'm not going to do it.

259
00:14:22.069 --> 00:14:23.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No dinner invitations, no flowers,

260
00:14:23.946 --> 00:14:27.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
no attempts at changing the nature
of our relationship.

261
00:14:27.491 --> 00:14:31.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until the current crisis has passed,
we both need our minds to be clear,

262
00:14:31.328 --> 00:14:34.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to be free of any
unnecessary distractions.

263
00:14:35.291 --> 00:14:36.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that's probably a good idea.

264
00:14:38.669 --> 00:14:41.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So for now,
all we need to concern ourselves with

265
00:14:41.630 --> 00:14:44.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is deploying the minefield,
maintaining station security,

266
00:14:44.925 --> 00:14:47.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and preparing ourselves
for a possible invasion.

267
00:14:47.303 --> 00:14:48.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm...

268
00:14:50.097 --> 00:14:52.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I don't know about you...

269
00:14:52.975 --> 00:14:55.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I feel more comfortable already.

270
00:14:56.562 --> 00:14:58.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

271
00:14:58.522 --> 00:14:59.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

272
00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:05.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Log, Stardate 50975.2.</i>

273
00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:08.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The next Jem'Hadar convoy </i>
<i>is due in five days,</i>

274
00:15:08.991 --> 00:15:11.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>but our efforts to mine the wormhole</i>

275
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:14.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>have already provoked</i>
<i>a response from the Dominion,</i>

276
00:15:14.705 --> 00:15:17.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>who have sent </i>
<i>their Vorta ambassador, Weyoun,</i>

277
00:15:17.166 --> 00:15:18.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to speak with me.</i>

278
00:15:21.045 --> 00:15:23.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What can I do for you, Weyoun?

279
00:15:23.589 --> 00:15:25.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain Sisko...

280
00:15:26.717 --> 00:15:28.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll make this brief.

281
00:15:29.345 --> 00:15:31.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We know all about the mine field.

282
00:15:31.180 --> 00:15:34.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I assumed you'd find out sooner or later.

283
00:15:34.224 --> 00:15:36.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As I see it, you have two choices.

284
00:15:37.519 --> 00:15:39.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Either you remove the mines,

285
00:15:39.688 --> 00:15:42.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or we will take this station from you

286
00:15:43.859 --> 00:15:45.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and remove them ourselves.

287
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:55.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I appreciate your directness.

288
00:15:55.704 --> 00:15:57.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, let me be direct with you.

289
00:15:57.831 --> 00:15:59.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The mines stay.

290
00:15:59.667 --> 00:16:01.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will not allow any more

291
00:16:01.210 --> 00:16:03.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dominion reinforcements
through the wormhole.

292
00:16:03.504 --> 00:16:06.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You will not allow?
-You heard me.

293
00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:12.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can see how that might be
your first reaction.

294
00:16:13.180 --> 00:16:17.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you and I are reasonable men.

295
00:16:17.393 --> 00:16:19.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And surely, reasonable men can come

296
00:16:19.770 --> 00:16:22.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to some sort of
mutually acceptable compromise.

297
00:16:22.398 --> 00:16:25.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't think the Dominion
believed in compromise.

298
00:16:25.234 --> 00:16:27.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

299
00:16:27.194 --> 00:16:30.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It saddens me to see how deeply
you misunderstand us.

300
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:32.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All the Dominion wants

301
00:16:32.408 --> 00:16:34.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to peacefully coexist
with its neighbors.

302
00:16:34.952 --> 00:16:37.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then why the continued military buildup?

303
00:16:37.413 --> 00:16:40.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why the weekly convoys of ships and troops
from the Gamma Quadrant?

304
00:16:43.919 --> 00:16:45.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the Cardassians.

305
00:16:46.046 --> 00:16:47.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't get me wrong.

306
00:16:47.715 --> 00:16:49.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm pleased to call them allies,

307
00:16:49.633 --> 00:16:52.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but as you know, they've just been through
a terrible war with the Klingons.

308
00:16:52.302 --> 00:16:55.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid it's left them
somewhat jittery,

309
00:16:56.056 --> 00:16:58.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so they're understandably
concerned about ensuring

310
00:16:58.976 --> 00:17:00.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the sovereignty of their borders.

311
00:17:00.728 --> 00:17:02.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And since they're now
members of the Dominion,

312
00:17:02.855 --> 00:17:05.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
their concerns have become our concerns.

313
00:17:06.066 --> 00:17:07.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I would think by now

314
00:17:07.651 --> 00:17:10.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you have more than enough ships
to defend Cardassia.

315
00:17:10.654 --> 00:17:13.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You may think that, and I may think that,
but the Cardassians--

316
00:17:13.657 --> 00:17:15.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, yes, I know. They're jittery.

317
00:17:16.035 --> 00:17:17.578  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You see our dilemma.

318
00:17:18.829 --> 00:17:19.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm beginning to.

319
00:17:22.499 --> 00:17:23.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if...

320
00:17:24.918 --> 00:17:29.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we agreed to limit our
convoys to cargo ships,

321
00:17:29.631 --> 00:17:31.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
construction units, civilian aid?

322
00:17:31.508 --> 00:17:34.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Things that will help them get
their economy back on its feet.

323
00:17:34.553 --> 00:17:39.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you know when we arrived
children were starving on Cardassia Prime?

324
00:17:39.850 --> 00:17:41.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was heartbreaking.

325
00:17:41.769 --> 00:17:44.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had no idea things were so bad.

326
00:17:45.898 --> 00:17:48.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Cardassians are a very proud people.

327
00:17:48.192 --> 00:17:51.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They don't want to admit to outsiders
how dire the situation really is.

328
00:17:53.739 --> 00:17:55.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So...

329
00:17:55.574 --> 00:17:57.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are we agreed?

330
00:17:57.201 --> 00:17:58.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You remove the mines,

331
00:17:58.869 --> 00:18:02.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we restrict our convoys
to medical and economic assistance.

332
00:18:02.873 --> 00:18:04.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That sounds reasonable.

333
00:18:04.416 --> 00:18:07.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd have to discuss it
with Starfleet first, of course.

334
00:18:07.961 --> 00:18:11.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure they'll do whatever
Benjamin Sisko recommends.

335
00:18:11.882 --> 00:18:15.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For my part,
I'll personally speak to the Founders

336
00:18:15.094 --> 00:18:16.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to secure our end of the bargain.

337
00:18:16.678 --> 00:18:18.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about Gul Dukat?

338
00:18:18.597 --> 00:18:20.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, he'll be furious...

339
00:18:21.266 --> 00:18:22.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at first.

340
00:18:23.268 --> 00:18:26.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we've developed
a fine working relationship,

341
00:18:26.438 --> 00:18:30.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I'm sure I can help him
to see the wisdom of our decision.

342
00:18:30.400 --> 00:18:33.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will leave it in your capable hands.

343
00:18:33.779 --> 00:18:35.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You won't be disappointed.

344
00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:43.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a momentous day.

345
00:18:43.622 --> 00:18:45.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You and I have just taken the first step

346
00:18:45.958 --> 00:18:49.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
towards insuring peace
between our peoples.

347
00:18:58.011 --> 00:19:00.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're going to attack.

348
00:19:00.139 --> 00:19:02.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you sure?
-I am positive.

349
00:19:02.307 --> 00:19:04.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The moment I mentioned
that we weren't going to remove the mines,

350
00:19:05.018 --> 00:19:06.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we both knew there'd be war.

351
00:19:06.770 --> 00:19:08.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything else was just words...

352
00:19:08.272 --> 00:19:11.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a feeble attempt to lull the other side
into a false sense of security.

353
00:19:11.358 --> 00:19:13.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't buy it,
and I'm sure Weyoun didn't either.

354
00:19:13.694 --> 00:19:15.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How soon?

355
00:19:15.195 --> 00:19:17.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As soon as they can get
their fleet from Cardassia.

356
00:19:17.364 --> 00:19:18.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd say as early as tomorrow.

357
00:19:19.616 --> 00:19:23.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which means we have to finish
the minefield today.

358
00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:24.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We need more time.</i>

359
00:19:24.580 --> 00:19:25.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't have it.

360
00:19:25.873 --> 00:19:28.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We'll do the best we can. Dax out.</i>

361
00:19:29.459 --> 00:19:32.504  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
General, take your ship
and patrol the border.

362
00:19:32.588 --> 00:19:34.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At the first sight
of the Dominion ships...

363
00:19:34.089 --> 00:19:35.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will sound the alarm.

364
00:19:35.799 --> 00:19:37.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't engage the enemy.

365
00:19:37.384 --> 00:19:39.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Get back to the station
as soon as you can.

366
00:19:39.136 --> 00:19:40.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're going to need you here.

367
00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:43.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, fighting them at the border
or fighting them here at the station

368
00:19:43.765 --> 00:19:45.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
makes no difference to me.

369
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:49.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't think
Starfleet could be persuaded

370
00:19:49.229 --> 00:19:52.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to send us a few more ships, say 50?

371
00:19:52.274 --> 00:19:54.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid not, Doctor. We're on our own.

372
00:19:54.902 --> 00:19:57.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In that case, I'd better go
and get the infirmary ready.

373
00:19:59.406 --> 00:20:02.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Worf, see to the weapons array
and issue combat assignments.

374
00:20:02.951 --> 00:20:04.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

375
00:20:04.328 --> 00:20:05.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major.

376
00:20:05.537 --> 00:20:08.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll contact the Bajoran Militia,
see if they can spare a few ships.

377
00:20:08.415 --> 00:20:09.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forget the Militia.

378
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:11.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need you to contact
the Council of Ministers.

379
00:20:11.710 --> 00:20:13.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell them I need to meet
with them immediately.

380
00:20:13.337 --> 00:20:16.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As a Starfleet Captain
or as the Emissary of the Prophets?

381
00:20:16.882 --> 00:20:17.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Both.

382
00:20:18.008 --> 00:20:19.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That'll get their attention.

383
00:20:19.176 --> 00:20:20.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember the nonaggression pact

384
00:20:20.677 --> 00:20:22.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Dominion offered Bajor
a few weeks ago?

385
00:20:22.596 --> 00:20:24.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, they're still debating it
in the Council of Ministers.

386
00:20:24.765 --> 00:20:26.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It'll never pass.

387
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:28.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It'll pass if the Emissary endorses it.

388
00:20:29.311 --> 00:20:32.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You want Bajor to sign a treaty
with the Dominion?

389
00:20:33.190 --> 00:20:34.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

390
00:20:36.193 --> 00:20:37.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major, when I came here,

391
00:20:37.402 --> 00:20:39.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my orders were to protect Bajor

392
00:20:39.196 --> 00:20:41.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and help your people
rebuild from the Occupation.

393
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:42.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've succeeded.

394
00:20:42.908 --> 00:20:46.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I refuse to see everything
we've accomplished torn down again.

395
00:20:48.163 --> 00:20:52.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The sad truth is, Major,
if there is a war now,

396
00:20:52.376 --> 00:20:55.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Federation can't guarantee
the safety of Bajor,

397
00:20:55.879 --> 00:20:58.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
which means Bajor must
be kept out of the fighting.

398
00:20:59.675 --> 00:21:02.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't like this
any more than you do, Major,

399
00:21:03.053 --> 00:21:05.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it's Bajor's only chance for survival.

400
00:21:07.766 --> 00:21:09.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

401
00:21:09.810 --> 00:21:12.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Bajor has signed the nonaggression pact</i>
<i>with the Dominion.</i>

402
00:21:12.271 --> 00:21:14.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All Bajoran personnel have been ordered</i>
<i>to evacuate the station.</i>

403
00:21:15.023 --> 00:21:16.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>As someone once said,</i>

404
00:21:16.650 --> 00:21:19.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>"These are the times </i>
<i>that try men's souls."</i>

405
00:21:20.320 --> 00:21:21.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ZIYAL: Are you sure you
won't come with me?

406
00:21:21.780 --> 00:21:23.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
GARAK: I don't think I'd be
very welcome on Bajor.

407
00:21:23.991 --> 00:21:26.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not going to be
very popular there, either.

408
00:21:26.368 --> 00:21:27.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My dear, you're half-Bajoran.

409
00:21:27.953 --> 00:21:30.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So at least half of you
is going to be accepted.

410
00:21:30.122 --> 00:21:33.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure that Major Kira's friends
will take good care of you.

411
00:21:34.501 --> 00:21:36.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, what's going to happen to you?

412
00:21:36.336 --> 00:21:38.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, well, let me tell you a story.

413
00:21:38.588 --> 00:21:40.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I once knew a Cardassian,

414
00:21:40.299 --> 00:21:43.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a dashing, handsome young man
with a promising career.

415
00:21:43.677 --> 00:21:45.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But one day, through no fault of his own,

416
00:21:45.804 --> 00:21:49.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he found himself exiled and alone
with nowhere to turn.

417
00:21:49.224 --> 00:21:51.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But did he give up?

418
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:52.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

419
00:21:53.228 --> 00:21:55.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He struck upon a brilliant plan.

420
00:21:55.939 --> 00:21:58.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Instead of fleeing
for the rest of his life,

421
00:21:58.233 --> 00:21:59.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he sought shelter

422
00:21:59.818 --> 00:22:03.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the one place no one
expected him to go...

423
00:22:03.113 --> 00:22:07.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in a stronghold of his
people's most hated enemies.

424
00:22:07.117 --> 00:22:10.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There, surrounded by hostile strangers,
he built a life.

425
00:22:10.662 --> 00:22:12.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And there, against all odds,

426
00:22:12.956 --> 00:22:16.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
against the merciless logic
of the universe itself,

427
00:22:17.586 --> 00:22:18.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he thrived.

428
00:22:19.004 --> 00:22:22.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By becoming the greatest tailor
in the galaxy.

429
00:22:22.466 --> 00:22:24.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the moral of the story, my dear,

430
00:22:25.052 --> 00:22:29.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to never underestimate
my gift for survival.

431
00:22:51.453 --> 00:22:53.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( speaking native language )

432
00:23:04.841 --> 00:23:06.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You may kiss the bride.

433
00:23:11.223 --> 00:23:13.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Congratulations, Father.

434
00:23:14.851 --> 00:23:16.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh... Moogie.

435
00:23:17.104 --> 00:23:18.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Nog.

436
00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:23.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you'll excuse me,
I have business to attend to.

437
00:23:28.824 --> 00:23:34.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that was the most pathetic excuse
for a wedding ceremony I've ever seen.

438
00:23:35.413 --> 00:23:38.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No bridal auction, no latinum dances,

439
00:23:38.291 --> 00:23:39.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and the bride...

440
00:23:39.668 --> 00:23:41.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the bride was severely overdressed.

441
00:23:41.711 --> 00:23:45.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nevertheless, you're very happy for us,
aren't you, Brother?

442
00:23:46.675 --> 00:23:48.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Overjoyed.

443
00:23:56.309 --> 00:23:57.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

444
00:23:59.146 --> 00:24:00.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I give it two months.

445
00:24:04.192 --> 00:24:05.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Rom.

446
00:24:05.986 --> 00:24:07.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No time for that.

447
00:24:07.445 --> 00:24:09.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nog, are Leeta's bags packed?

448
00:24:09.406 --> 00:24:10.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're already on the shuttle.

449
00:24:10.740 --> 00:24:12.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You mean we're leaving?
-No.

450
00:24:12.951 --> 00:24:14.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're leaving.

451
00:24:14.411 --> 00:24:16.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First Minister Shakaar was very clear.

452
00:24:16.413 --> 00:24:19.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All Bajorans must leave the station
for their own safety.

453
00:24:19.624 --> 00:24:20.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But what about you?

454
00:24:20.834 --> 00:24:23.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My job is here, with Chief O'Brien.

455
00:24:23.128 --> 00:24:24.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then I'm not going either.

456
00:24:24.754 --> 00:24:26.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You see that, Nog?

457
00:24:26.256 --> 00:24:31.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've barely finished saying our vows,
and we're already having our first fight.

458
00:24:31.094 --> 00:24:33.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're really married.

459
00:24:34.055 --> 00:24:35.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've got to go, Leeta.

460
00:24:35.807 --> 00:24:37.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The problems of two newlyweds

461
00:24:37.726 --> 00:24:41.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
are but a small thread
in the tapestry of galactic events.

462
00:24:41.438 --> 00:24:44.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You might not understand that today,
or even tomorrow,

463
00:24:44.566 --> 00:24:47.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but someday you will.

464
00:24:47.402 --> 00:24:51.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So get on that shuttle
and don't look back.

465
00:24:51.907 --> 00:24:54.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nog, take your Moogie to the Docking Ring.

466
00:24:57.662 --> 00:24:59.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice speech, Dad.

467
00:25:04.169 --> 00:25:05.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought so.

468
00:25:08.131 --> 00:25:12.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, what's the status
of program Sisko-1-9-7?

469
00:25:12.427 --> 00:25:15.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
COMPUTER: <i>All necessary modifications</i>
<i>have been completed.</i>

470
00:25:15.222 --> 00:25:18.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Program Sisko-1-9-7 </i>
<i>ready for implementation</i>

471
00:25:18.642 --> 00:25:19.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>on your command.</i>

472
00:25:19.935 --> 00:25:21.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NOG: <i>Ops to Captain Sisko.</i>

473
00:25:21.853 --> 00:25:24.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Sir, we're receiving a message</i>
<i>from the Cardassian border.</i>

474
00:25:24.648 --> 00:25:26.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's General Martok.</i>

475
00:25:28.568 --> 00:25:29.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On screen.

476
00:25:29.819 --> 00:25:31.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

477
00:25:32.322 --> 00:25:33.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MARTOK: <i>Captain, we just detected</i>

478
00:25:33.949 --> 00:25:37.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a large force of Dominion ships</i>
<i>headed your way.</i>

479
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:39.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>They should be there within the hou--</i>

480
00:25:42.290 --> 00:25:44.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone is jamming his transmission.

481
00:25:45.085 --> 00:25:46.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Contact established.</i>

482
00:25:47.087 --> 00:25:48.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DUKAT: <i>Captain Sisko,</i>

483
00:25:48.380 --> 00:25:51.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I don't suppose </i>
<i>you would like to surrender</i>

484
00:25:51.466 --> 00:25:53.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and avoid unnecessary bloodshed.</i>

485
00:25:56.179 --> 00:25:57.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Absolutely not.

486
00:25:57.931 --> 00:26:00.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I was hoping you'd say that.</i>

487
00:26:04.271 --> 00:26:05.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Battle stations.

488
00:26:09.901 --> 00:26:14.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( alarm blaring )

489
00:26:14.406 --> 00:26:15.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How much longer?

490
00:26:15.532 --> 00:26:17.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Dominion fleet
should be in weapons range in 20 minutes.

491
00:26:17.909 --> 00:26:19.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are all the Bajorans off the station?

492
00:26:19.327 --> 00:26:21.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NOG: The last transport just left.

493
00:26:21.371 --> 00:26:24.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Let's hope the Dominion honors
the nonaggression pact.

494
00:26:26.042 --> 00:26:28.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Cadet, put me through to the <i>Defiant.</i>

495
00:26:28.878 --> 00:26:29.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

496
00:26:30.046 --> 00:26:31.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On screen.

497
00:26:31.756 --> 00:26:33.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Benjamin, I know what you're going to say,

498
00:26:33.967 --> 00:26:35.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we've got at least
another hour of work

499
00:26:35.760 --> 00:26:37.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before we can activate the minefield.

500
00:26:37.262 --> 00:26:39.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You don't have an hour, old man.</i>

501
00:26:39.347 --> 00:26:41.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Dominion is going to be here</i>
<i>in less than 20 minutes.</i>

502
00:26:41.766 --> 00:26:43.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You're going to be a sitting duck.</i>

503
00:26:43.184 --> 00:26:45.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then I hope you can buy us some more time.

504
00:26:45.895 --> 00:26:47.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax out.

505
00:26:48.231 --> 00:26:49.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax to O'Brien.

506
00:26:49.649 --> 00:26:52.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know, I know. Work faster.

507
00:26:52.444 --> 00:26:55.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
JAKE: A medical tricorder, hypospray,
dermal regenerator,

508
00:26:55.447 --> 00:26:58.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and battlefield trauma kit.

509
00:26:58.491 --> 00:27:01.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Medical tricorder, hypospray
dermal regenerator,

510
00:27:01.411 --> 00:27:02.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and battlefield trauma kit.

511
00:27:04.039 --> 00:27:05.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) That's everyone.

512
00:27:05.665 --> 00:27:07.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now what?

513
00:27:08.335 --> 00:27:10.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now we wait...

514
00:27:11.921 --> 00:27:14.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
until the casualties start coming in.

515
00:27:15.967 --> 00:27:17.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure you're all right?

516
00:27:18.345 --> 00:27:19.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be fine.

517
00:27:19.846 --> 00:27:21.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Besides, my father
won't let me stay in Ops,

518
00:27:21.765 --> 00:27:24.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and, uh,
I promised the Federation News Service

519
00:27:24.184 --> 00:27:26.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a firsthand account of the battle.

520
00:27:26.144 --> 00:27:27.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll get it.

521
00:27:27.812 --> 00:27:31.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just remember,
Bashir is spelled with an "I."

522
00:27:39.491 --> 00:27:43.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I must say, Constable,
I admire your composure.

523
00:27:44.079 --> 00:27:47.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're an island of tranquility
in a sea of chaos.

524
00:27:47.624 --> 00:27:49.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What I am is useless.

525
00:27:49.459 --> 00:27:52.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My entire staff
has been evacuated to Bajor.

526
00:27:52.337 --> 00:27:55.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not feeling too terribly
useful myself at this moment.

527
00:27:55.715 --> 00:27:58.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if it'd make you feel any better,
you could always deputize me.

528
00:27:59.052 --> 00:28:00.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( scoffs )

529
00:28:00.512 --> 00:28:03.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure if the Jem'Hadar
board the station,

530
00:28:03.223 --> 00:28:05.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'll make yourself useful.

531
00:28:05.141 --> 00:28:06.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's ironic.

532
00:28:07.394 --> 00:28:09.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When the Klingons attacked the station,

533
00:28:09.354 --> 00:28:11.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Gul Dukat and I
were fighting side by side.

534
00:28:11.689 --> 00:28:13.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At one point, he turned his back to me,

535
00:28:13.650 --> 00:28:19.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I must admit that for a moment,
he made a very tempting target.

536
00:28:19.989 --> 00:28:22.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'd shoot a man in the back?

537
00:28:22.117 --> 00:28:24.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it's the safest way, isn't it?

538
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:25.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But then I thought,

539
00:28:25.620 --> 00:28:28.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Well, no, I can't fight
all these Klingons by myself,"

540
00:28:28.873 --> 00:28:30.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so I let him live.

541
00:28:30.291 --> 00:28:32.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now you regret it.

542
00:28:32.293 --> 00:28:36.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ah, my dear Constable,
before this day is over,

543
00:28:36.172 --> 00:28:39.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
everyone on this station
is going to regret it.

544
00:28:40.009 --> 00:28:41.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device whirring )

545
00:28:41.511 --> 00:28:43.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom...

546
00:28:43.763 --> 00:28:45.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've always said you were an idiot,

547
00:28:45.348 --> 00:28:47.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I never believed it
more than I do at this moment.

548
00:28:47.684 --> 00:28:49.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Brother, if you want to insult me,
it's going to have to wait till later.

549
00:28:49.686 --> 00:28:50.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm busy.

550
00:28:50.687 --> 00:28:51.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Busy doing what?

551
00:28:52.063 --> 00:28:54.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Preparing perimeter defenses
for the attack.

552
00:28:55.233 --> 00:28:58.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are dozens of engineers
that could be doing that.

553
00:28:58.945 --> 00:29:02.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Starfleet engineers.

554
00:29:02.115 --> 00:29:03.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hu-mans.

555
00:29:03.533 --> 00:29:05.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device turns off )

556
00:29:05.201 --> 00:29:07.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should be on Bajor with your new wife.

557
00:29:07.662 --> 00:29:09.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what Leeta said.

558
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:12.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, she's right. This is not your fight.

559
00:29:12.292 --> 00:29:14.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not your fight either,
but I don't see you leaving.

560
00:29:14.627 --> 00:29:17.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to look out for my bar.

561
00:29:17.338 --> 00:29:19.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I have to look out for you.

562
00:29:19.299 --> 00:29:21.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Me?
-You're my brother.

563
00:29:21.634 --> 00:29:24.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever happens, we belong together.

564
00:29:29.267 --> 00:29:30.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device starts up )

565
00:29:32.604 --> 00:29:35.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, like I said, you're an idiot.

566
00:29:43.573 --> 00:29:45.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NOG: On screen, Captain.

567
00:29:45.408 --> 00:29:48.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
General Martok, take a defensive
position near the <i>Defiant.</i>

568
00:29:48.328 --> 00:29:50.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have to finish deploying those mines
no matter the cost.

569
00:29:50.997 --> 00:29:52.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And they will.</i>

570
00:29:52.290 --> 00:29:54.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You have my word on it, Captain.</i>

571
00:29:56.795 --> 00:29:59.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, activate the weapons array.

572
00:29:59.130 --> 00:30:00.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

573
00:30:09.641 --> 00:30:12.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, as a Major
in the Bajoran Militia,

574
00:30:12.644 --> 00:30:15.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I must officially protest
Starfleet's refusal

575
00:30:15.396 --> 00:30:17.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to turn over this station
to my government.

576
00:30:17.273 --> 00:30:19.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Your protest is duly noted.
-Good.

577
00:30:19.484 --> 00:30:21.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now that that's over with...

578
00:30:21.778 --> 00:30:24.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kira Nerys reporting for duty.

579
00:30:43.049 --> 00:30:44.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Weapons range in one minute.

580
00:30:46.594 --> 00:30:49.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been waiting for this moment
for five years.

581
00:30:49.639 --> 00:30:52.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First, we reclaim Terok Nor,

582
00:30:52.809 --> 00:30:55.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then... on to Bajor.

583
00:30:55.562 --> 00:30:57.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

584
00:30:57.230 --> 00:30:59.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Or must I remind you
the Dominion just signed

585
00:30:59.399 --> 00:31:01.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a nonaggression pact with Bajor?

586
00:31:01.150 --> 00:31:02.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion might have.

587
00:31:02.986 --> 00:31:04.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never did.

588
00:31:05.530 --> 00:31:07.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion will honor its treaty,

589
00:31:07.699 --> 00:31:11.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and as a member of the Dominion,
you will honor it as well.

590
00:31:14.205 --> 00:31:17.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where the Dominion leads, I will follow.

591
00:31:17.458 --> 00:31:19.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never doubted it.

592
00:31:19.586 --> 00:31:24.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Attack wings one through five,
head for the <i>Defiant.</i>

593
00:31:24.299 --> 00:31:28.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remaining ships, target the station.

594
00:31:33.641 --> 00:31:35.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're within weapons range.

595
00:31:35.143 --> 00:31:36.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

596
00:31:36.895 --> 00:31:38.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then by all means...

597
00:31:40.440 --> 00:31:41.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fire.

598
00:31:46.905 --> 00:31:49.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, all weapons fire at will.

599
00:32:13.473 --> 00:32:15.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Enemy ships are closing on the <i>Defiant.</i>

600
00:32:16.059 --> 00:32:17.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Mr. Worf.
-Got them.

601
00:32:23.650 --> 00:32:27.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( console beeping )
-Sir, the station's shields are holding.

602
00:32:27.362 --> 00:32:28.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Impossible.

603
00:32:28.363 --> 00:32:31.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Federation shields have always proven
useless against our weapons.

604
00:32:31.616 --> 00:32:35.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've found it wise to never underestimate
the Federation's technical skill

605
00:32:36.663 --> 00:32:39.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or Captain Sisko's resourcefulness.

606
00:32:39.582 --> 00:32:41.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damar, bring us around for another pass.

607
00:32:59.894 --> 00:33:01.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief, how much longer?

608
00:33:01.354 --> 00:33:02.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: <i>Just another couple of minutes.</i>

609
00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:05.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take us to our final set of coordinates.

610
00:33:05.274 --> 00:33:06.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Helm, set course--

611
00:33:14.450 --> 00:33:16.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, I'm going to have to take
evasive maneuvers.

612
00:33:18.246 --> 00:33:21.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you do, you risk setting off
every mine on this ship.

613
00:33:21.124 --> 00:33:22.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yells )

614
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:26.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if I don't,
we may not have a ship left!

615
00:33:37.390 --> 00:33:39.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You may continue your work, Commander.</i>

616
00:33:39.726 --> 00:33:42.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I will handle the Jem'Hadar.</i>

617
00:33:42.854 --> 00:33:45.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Who says there's never a Klingon around
when you need one?

618
00:33:45.940 --> 00:33:47.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckling )

619
00:33:51.362 --> 00:33:52.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shields at 35%.

620
00:33:53.948 --> 00:33:55.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're preparing for another attack.

621
00:33:56.951 --> 00:33:59.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, make every shot count.

622
00:33:59.454 --> 00:34:01.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Attack wings and batteries,

623
00:34:01.831 --> 00:34:06.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
concentrate your firepower on Section 17
of the Outer Docking Ring.

624
00:34:06.669 --> 00:34:09.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have to penetrate their shields.

625
00:34:31.319 --> 00:34:33.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've lost main power to the shields.

626
00:34:33.488 --> 00:34:36.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Switching to auxiliary power,
but I do not know how long it will hold.

627
00:34:37.533 --> 00:34:38.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yelling )

628
00:34:40.578 --> 00:34:42.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
-DAX:<i> </i>Defiant<i> to Captain Sisko.</i>

629
00:34:42.663 --> 00:34:43.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax, go ahead.

630
00:34:43.748 --> 00:34:45.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've set the last mine.

631
00:34:45.416 --> 00:34:47.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Activate the field and return
to the station.

632
00:34:47.585 --> 00:34:48.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Yes, sir. Dax out.</i>

633
00:34:58.262 --> 00:35:01.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sir, the minefields--
-I have eyes, Damar.

634
00:35:01.474 --> 00:35:03.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This isn't turning out
quite the way I had planned.

635
00:35:03.976 --> 00:35:06.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a minor setback, Weyoun.

636
00:35:06.562 --> 00:35:08.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Once we take the station,

637
00:35:08.189 --> 00:35:11.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we'll be able to dismantle the minefield
without interference.

638
00:35:11.150 --> 00:35:13.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's both hope your
confidence is justified.

639
00:35:15.822 --> 00:35:20.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damar, signal the reserves
to prepare for a final assault.

640
00:35:22.495 --> 00:35:24.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion fleet is regrouping.

641
00:35:24.288 --> 00:35:25.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( console beeping )

642
00:35:25.623 --> 00:35:29.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I'm detecting another wave
of enemy ships entering Bajoran space.

643
00:35:29.085 --> 00:35:30.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are your orders, Captain?

644
00:35:31.129 --> 00:35:32.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've done all we can here.

645
00:35:33.589 --> 00:35:36.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Notify all remaining Starfleet personnel.

646
00:35:37.510 --> 00:35:40.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're evacuating the station.

647
00:35:49.981 --> 00:35:51.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MAN: Report to the staging area.

648
00:35:54.986 --> 00:35:56.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAX: Worf!

649
00:35:56.279 --> 00:35:57.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia.

650
00:35:57.780 --> 00:35:59.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should be on the <i>Defiant.</i>

651
00:36:00.199 --> 00:36:01.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I heard you're not coming with us,

652
00:36:01.659 --> 00:36:03.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you've been assigned
to Martok's ship.

653
00:36:03.161 --> 00:36:05.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It may be some time
before we see each other again.

654
00:36:05.288 --> 00:36:07.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, we may never see each other again.

655
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:10.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is war.
We must put aside our personal feelings

656
00:36:10.376 --> 00:36:12.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and focus on the task at hand.

657
00:36:12.170 --> 00:36:15.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been through my share of wars.
I know what I have to do.

658
00:36:15.214 --> 00:36:17.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But before you leave,

659
00:36:17.717 --> 00:36:20.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to know
that the answer is "yes."

660
00:36:20.094 --> 00:36:22.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes... Yes to what?

661
00:36:22.263 --> 00:36:24.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I will marry you.

662
00:36:24.348 --> 00:36:27.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's what you've wanted
from the beginning, isn't it?

663
00:36:27.602 --> 00:36:29.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

664
00:36:29.437 --> 00:36:30.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, it is.

665
00:36:30.980 --> 00:36:34.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then when all of this is over,
we'll get married.

666
00:36:34.734 --> 00:36:38.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if that doesn't
give you a reason to survive,

667
00:36:38.696 --> 00:36:40.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what will.

668
00:36:54.545 --> 00:36:59.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I first took command of this post,
all I wanted was to be somewhere else...

669
00:36:59.425 --> 00:37:01.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
anywhere but here.

670
00:37:01.761 --> 00:37:03.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But now, five years later,

671
00:37:03.804 --> 00:37:07.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
this has become my home,
and you have become my family.

672
00:37:07.892 --> 00:37:09.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And leaving this station... leaving you...

673
00:37:09.977 --> 00:37:13.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is one of the hardest things
I've ever had to do.

674
00:37:13.648 --> 00:37:16.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But this war isn't over yet.</i>

675
00:37:16.901 --> 00:37:20.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I want you to know that while we were </i>
<i>keeping the Dominion occupied,</i>

676
00:37:20.613 --> 00:37:24.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a Starfleet-Klingon task force</i>
<i>crossed the border into Cardassia</i>

677
00:37:24.533 --> 00:37:27.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and destroyed the Dominion
shipyards on Torros III.

678
00:37:27.870 --> 00:37:29.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your sacrifices...

679
00:37:29.538 --> 00:37:32.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our sacrifices made that victory possible.

680
00:37:34.710 --> 00:37:39.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But no victory can make
this moment any easier for me.

681
00:37:40.591 --> 00:37:44.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I promise, I will not rest

682
00:37:44.387 --> 00:37:47.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
until I stand with you again...

683
00:37:47.682 --> 00:37:50.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
here...

684
00:37:50.351 --> 00:37:52.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in this place where I belong.

685
00:37:57.400 --> 00:37:59.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko to <i>Defiant.</i>

686
00:37:59.485 --> 00:38:00.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: <i>Standing by, sir.</i>

687
00:38:02.196 --> 00:38:05.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-One to beam aboard.
<i>-Aye, Captain.</i>

688
00:38:12.373 --> 00:38:14.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are we ready?
-As soon as you give the word, sir.

689
00:38:15.626 --> 00:38:16.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Garak?

690
00:38:16.919 --> 00:38:18.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to come along, if you don't mind.

691
00:38:18.671 --> 00:38:21.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never know when you
might need a good tailor.

692
00:38:21.132 --> 00:38:24.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the simple fact is,
I have nowhere else to go.

693
00:38:24.760 --> 00:38:25.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome aboard.

694
00:38:26.053 --> 00:38:27.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beeping )
<i>-Dax to Sisko.</i>

695
00:38:27.805 --> 00:38:30.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Dominion fleet</i>
<i>is coming around for another attack.</i>

696
00:38:30.766 --> 00:38:33.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Release docking clamps.
Prepare for departure.

697
00:38:52.580 --> 00:38:53.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( console beeping )

698
00:38:54.498 --> 00:38:55.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The <i>Defiant's </i>away.

699
00:38:57.084 --> 00:38:58.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Contact the Dominion fleet.

700
00:38:58.711 --> 00:39:00.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell them...

701
00:39:00.463 --> 00:39:03.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Bajoran government
welcomes them to <i>Deep Space 9.</i>

702
00:39:04.884 --> 00:39:07.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( console beeps )
-Message acknowledged.

703
00:39:07.386 --> 00:39:08.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good.

704
00:39:08.679 --> 00:39:11.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's the last message this station
will be sending out for a while.

705
00:39:11.766 --> 00:39:12.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer...

706
00:39:13.017 --> 00:39:15.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
initiate program Sisko-1-9-7.

707
00:39:15.978 --> 00:39:17.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
COMPUTER: <i>Program initiated.</i>

708
00:39:34.830 --> 00:39:37.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dukat wanted the station back.
He can have it.

709
00:39:39.585 --> 00:39:42.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't want to see a drop of root beer
left in this place.

710
00:39:42.838 --> 00:39:44.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Break out the kanar.

711
00:39:44.799 --> 00:39:47.093  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And find me some yamok sauce.

712
00:39:48.260 --> 00:39:49.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom...

713
00:39:49.345 --> 00:39:52.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
assistant manager
for policy and clientele.

714
00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:53.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Reporting for work, Brother.

715
00:39:54.058 --> 00:39:55.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What, did you think you could
just walk back in here

716
00:39:55.976 --> 00:39:57.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and get your old job back?

717
00:39:57.436 --> 00:39:59.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I'm a spy...
working for Starfleet.

718
00:39:59.980 --> 00:40:01.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But don't tell anyone.

719
00:40:02.233 --> 00:40:04.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( quietly ) The Federation's
more desperate than I thought.

720
00:40:06.320 --> 00:40:09.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( aloud ) I knew one day
you'd come crawling back to me.

721
00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:11.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Now, get to work.
-Yes, Brother!

722
00:40:21.419 --> 00:40:22.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake?

723
00:40:22.711 --> 00:40:24.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aren't you supposed to be on the <i>Defiant?</i>

724
00:40:25.005 --> 00:40:26.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I changed my mind.

725
00:40:27.299 --> 00:40:29.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a war going on and...

726
00:40:29.552 --> 00:40:31.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a reporter.

727
00:40:31.345 --> 00:40:32.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is where I belong.

728
00:40:38.310 --> 00:40:39.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you're not safe here.

729
00:40:42.106 --> 00:40:45.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion knows I'm the Emissary's son.

730
00:40:45.234 --> 00:40:46.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If they hurt me,

731
00:40:46.402 --> 00:40:49.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they risk alienating their new friends,
the Bajorans.

732
00:40:51.699 --> 00:40:52.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hope you're right.

733
00:40:54.743 --> 00:40:55.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So do I.

734
00:40:56.412 --> 00:40:58.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell is Jake thinking?

735
00:40:58.789 --> 00:41:00.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do we go back for him?

736
00:41:00.374 --> 00:41:02.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't risk the entire crew
for one man...

737
00:41:02.501 --> 00:41:04.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
even though he is my son.

738
00:41:04.503 --> 00:41:07.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And whether I like it or not, he is a man,

739
00:41:07.756 --> 00:41:10.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
capable of making his own choices.

740
00:41:13.804 --> 00:41:15.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maintain current course.

741
00:41:16.390 --> 00:41:18.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, Captain.

742
00:41:18.642 --> 00:41:22.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We should rendezvous with the Federation
task force in 48 hours.

743
00:41:22.605 --> 00:41:23.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then what?

744
00:41:23.814 --> 00:41:27.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And then, we make the Dominion sorry
they ever set foot in the Alpha Quadrant.

745
00:41:27.276 --> 00:41:30.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Cadet, you took the words
right out of my mouth.

746
00:41:47.546 --> 00:41:50.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a great victory for Cardassia.

747
00:41:50.341 --> 00:41:52.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the Dominion.

748
00:41:52.176 --> 00:41:54.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Over 50 ships lost...

749
00:41:54.386 --> 00:41:56.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our spacedocks on Torros III destroyed.

750
00:41:57.056 --> 00:41:59.058  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A victory perhaps, but a costly one.

751
00:41:59.141 --> 00:42:01.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll discuss the repercussions later.

752
00:42:01.936 --> 00:42:05.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right now, I'm going to enjoy this moment.

753
00:42:07.733 --> 00:42:11.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Gentlemen,
on behalf of the Bajoran government--

754
00:42:11.111 --> 00:42:13.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the Promenade
Merchants' Association...

755
00:42:13.447 --> 00:42:16.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I officially welcome you to <i>Deep Space 9.</i>

756
00:42:16.951 --> 00:42:20.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean... <i>Terok Nor,</i> don't you?

757
00:42:24.375 --> 00:42:28.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Founder, we are honored
by your decision to remain with us.

758
00:42:28.379 --> 00:42:30.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not here as a Founder.

759
00:42:30.339 --> 00:42:32.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm the station's Chief of Security.

760
00:42:34.051 --> 00:42:35.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever you say.

761
00:42:35.261 --> 00:42:39.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nevertheless, having a God walk amongst us
is most gratifying.

762
00:42:39.557 --> 00:42:41.016  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I agree.

763
00:42:41.934 --> 00:42:44.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You... me...

764
00:42:45.646 --> 00:42:46.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the Major...

765
00:42:47.022 --> 00:42:49.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
together again.

766
00:42:49.358 --> 00:42:51.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should be most interesting.

767
00:42:52.486 --> 00:42:55.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'll be in my office.

768
00:43:06.125 --> 00:43:08.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( static and hissing )

769
00:43:11.255 --> 00:43:14.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would appear
Captain Sisko was most efficient

770
00:43:14.925 --> 00:43:16.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in disabling the station.

771
00:43:16.719 --> 00:43:18.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It can be repaired.

772
00:43:18.470 --> 00:43:19.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And it will be.

773
00:43:19.805 --> 00:43:22.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But your first priority
is to dismantle that minefield.

774
00:43:23.017 --> 00:43:26.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until we can bring in
reinforcements from the Gamma Quadrant,

775
00:43:26.145 --> 00:43:27.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our position here is vulnerable.

776
00:43:27.354 --> 00:43:29.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll deal with the minefields.

777
00:43:37.990 --> 00:43:42.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I assume Captain Sisko removed
or destroyed everything of value.

778
00:43:43.746 --> 00:43:45.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not everything.

779
00:43:50.544 --> 00:43:51.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is that?

780
00:43:52.921 --> 00:43:55.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A message... from Sisko.

781
00:43:55.883 --> 00:43:57.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't understand.

782
00:43:57.593 --> 00:43:59.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

783
00:43:59.178 --> 00:44:01.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's letting me know...

784
00:44:03.223 --> 00:44:05.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He'll be back.

